President Muhammadu Buhari has met with the National Leader of the All Progressives Congress (APC), Asiwaju Bola Tinubu.  The meeting took place today at the Presidential Villa, Abuja. The meeting, which agenda could not be ascertained as at the time of filing this report, is believed to be a courtesy one. The meeting is coming on the heels of fresh disagreements among leaders of the ruling party threatening the conduct of the long-awaited National Convention. Tinubu is believed to be a front-runner in the race for the party’s presidential ticket. Details shortly…  Source The President, Muhammadu Buhari (retd.), met with the National Leader of the All Progressives Congress, Bola Tinubu, in Aso Rock on Sunday. The meeting was held behind closed doors. After the meeting, Tinubu said he visited to thank the president for checking on him in London after having knee surgery.… In "Politics" The National leader of the All Progressives Congress, Bola Tinubu has welcomed Professor Ibrahim Gambari, the Chief of Staff to President Muhammadu Buhari to his home. Gambari visited Tinubu at his Asokoro residence in Abuja on Monday, few hours after the APC leader visited President Buhari in Aso Rock. Speaking… In "News" By Ismaila Chafe Abuja -   President Muhammadu Buhari on Monday met behind closed door with a chieftain of the All Progressives Congress (APC), Sen. Bola Tinubu, in the Presidential Villa, Abuja. The News Agency of Nigeria (NAN) reports that before his meeting with Tinubu, Buhari had earlier met with… In "Top Stories"